@yalelawschool #yale

Bill DeWitt III ’90, president of the St. Louis @Cardinals, recalls the team’s historic come-from-behind victory in Game 6 of the 2011 World Series.

Hear the full conversation with his father, Bill DeWitt Jr. ’63, the team’s chairman and CEO, and President Peter Salovey — about leadership lessons from the pandemic, @YaleAthletics, and the rise of sabermetrics — all in the latest Yale Talk podcast: president.yale.edu/yale-talk

Class Day speaker and double-EGOT composer Bobby Lopez ’97 created “The Beacon” specifically for the Harkness Tower carillon. 

Lopez is the songwriter behind “Frozen,” “Coco,” “Avenue Q,” and “Book of Mormon.”

The Beacon was played during today’s Class Day ceremony by graduate Paul Stelben ’21, the only carillonneur in Yale’s history to be certified by the Guild of Carillonneurs in North America, which he achieved as a sophomore.

Experience all the Class Day traditions and festivities, including more musical performances, at yale2021.yale.edu

#YaleAlumni #Yale2021

node.text:
Yale Class Day begins now! Watch the full ceremony at: yale2021.yale.edu/class-day

Yale Glee Club came together in person for the first time in over a year to lend their voices to several favorite pieces from the group’s repertoire, including “Alleluia,” “Bright College Years,” and this piece — “Raise Your Voices Here” by @yalegleeclub Director Jeffrey Douma. 

The ceremony will include these performances, reflections from the graduating class, an address by songwriter Robert Lopez ’97, and many other traditions dating back to Class Day’s origins in the 19th century.

Last week, incoming first-year students moved their belongings onto campus and quickly departed to attend Harvest, a pre-orientation program at family-owned farms across Connecticut. 

It's an experience that stays with students long after the week is over. During the day, they harvested fruits and planted fall crops. They spent evenings cooling off in a pond, gathering around a fire, and camping with fellow members of the Class of #Yale2025. 

@yaleharvest is run by the Yale Sustainable Food Program (@ysfp)

node.text:
At Opening Assembly on Saturday morning, Yale President Peter Salovey (📷 5) and Yale College Dean Marvin Chun (📷 3) welcomed 1,800 members of the Yale Class of 2025 as they formally began their collegiate experience.
 
The outdoor ceremony on Cross Campus was held in-person for the first time since 2019.
 
Dean Chun remarked:
 
“You do not have to count on any test, assignment, or grade to prove your worth. What’s important now is to enjoy the process of learning and being in community with each other.
 
“Let me assume that you have come here not only to find knowledge but also to learn how to live lives of consequence.
 
If that is true, you have come to the right place. As you take your first steps, then, you will need to become comfortable with difference, not just to accept it or tolerate it but to insist on it.
 
“You will find guides everywhere, in the classes you will take, the activities you join, and most of all from the people joining you right now — your peers and classmates. All of them are part of the liberal arts education that awaits you.”
 
Welcome, Class of #Yale2025!
 
#yale
